[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 471 417 with 81 285 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 390 132 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 201 countries/locations outside mainland China representing an increase of 48 521 cases when compared with the data on 24 Mar 2020, with the USA accounting for 13 554 (27.9%) cases, Italy accounting for 5210 (10.7%) cases, and Spain for 7457 (15.4%) of the newly confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside of China now represents 82.8% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 14.5% of the global cases of COVID-19. With the rate of growth of confirmed cases in the USA, within the next 24 hours, the total number of reported cases in the USA will surpass the total number reported in China. Italy will surpass the China total within the next 48 hours. A global total of 21 295 deaths have been reported, 18 008 outside mainland China.

It is now clear that while China has the largest population in the world, and was the original location where the COVID-19 outbreak started, it has markedly reduced transmission to a manageable level, now monitoring all arrivals in the country from outside. South Korea has slowly decreased daily new case counts hovering around or below 100 in recent days. Within 1-2 days, the USA will be number one outside of China for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19 and Italy and Iran will drop back in their rankings. I repeat my request to see epidemic curves by date of onset to see what the true curve of transmission is, as I suspect now that more testing is being done, many of those tested have been sick for days while awaiting testing. - Mod.MPP]

