[2] China: National Health Commission 25 Mar 2020
Date: Wed 25 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/f01fc26a8a7b48debe194bd1277fdba3.shtml


At 04:00 on [25 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 67 new confirmed cases, all of which were imported cases; 6 new deaths; and 58 new suspected cases. All are imported cases.

On the same day, 401 cases were cured and discharged, 721 were close contacts of medical observation, and 164 severe cases were reduced.

As of 24:00 on [25 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 3947 confirmed cases (among which, 1235 were severe cases), 74 051 cases were cured and 3287 cases were fatal. A total of 81 285 confirmed cases have been reported, and there are currently 159 suspected cases. A total of 695 305 close contacts were traced, and 14,714 were close contacts in medical observation.

There were 0 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (0 in Wuhan), 391 newly cured cases (382 in Wuhan), 6 new deaths (5 in Wuhan), and 3341 confirmed cases (3407 in Wuhan). Among them, 1201 were severe cases (1195 in Wuhan). A total of 61 201 discharged patients were cured (44 068 in Wuhan), a total of 3169 deaths (in Wuhan, 2531), and a total of 67 801 confirmed cases (in Wuhan, 6506). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 in Wuhan) and 0 existing suspected cases (0 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [25 Mar 2020], 67 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported (18 in Shanghai, 12 in Inner Mongolia, 11 in Guangdong, 6 in Beijing, 6 in Fujian, 3 in Shaanxi, 2 in Tianjin, and 2 in Zhejiang), 2 cases in Jiangsu, 2 cases in Yunnan, 1 case in Shanxi, 1 case in Jilin, and 1 case in Henan). As of 24:00 on [25 Mar 2020], a total of 541 confirmed imported cases were reported overseas.

A total of 675 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 410 cases in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (106 cases discharged, 4 deaths), 30 cases in Macau Special Administrative Region (10 cases discharged), 235 cases in Taiwan (29 cases discharged, 2 deaths) ).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[This is the 2nd consecutive day with no newly confirmed cases reported from Wuhan or all of Hubei province in the past 24 hours, and also no suspected cases reported. This is a major milestone and the 2nd day zero cases, neither confirmed nor suspected, were identified. There are 67 newly confirmed cases reported to have been confirmed in the past 24 hours elsewhere in China, with all 67 identified as imported cases.

According to the report above, a total of 81 285 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, representing an increase of 67 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (24 Mar 2020) report was prepared. In addition, 6 deaths were reported, all in Hubei province (5 in Wuhan). 24 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, which bears watching as the cases have been slowly but steadily climbing. And Macau reported 4 additional newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, bringing their total to 30.

All 67 newly confirmed cases were imported cases into China. Cases were reported by Shanghai (18), Inner Mongolia (12), Guangdong (11), Beijing (6), Fujian (6), Shaanxi (3), Tianjin (2), Zhejiang (2), Yunnan (2), Jiangsu (2), Shanxi (1), Jilin (1), and Henan (1). bringing the total number of imported cases to 541.

As reported yesterday (24 Mar 2020), China is ending the lockdown in Hubei now, and will end it in Wuhan on 6 Apr 2020. There is much caution and skepticism in the media over the reality of the zero case reports. There are claims that there continue to be asymptomatic positive individuals, an indicator that the virus is still circulating. If these rumors have validity, there will most likely be a recrudescence of transmission, but should that happen, presumably the public health structure in China will be activated and ready to prevent a repeat overwhelming situation as seen in January and February 2020. The world will be watching carefully to see if this is safe timing...

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7143838,155. - Mod.MPP]

