Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 104 cases and 5 deaths as compared with yesterday's 24 hour period (24-25 Mar 2020) when there were 100 newly confirmed cases. The daily case count has been at or below 100 newly confirmed cases per day for 5 consecutive days. Daegu continues to stand out as a focal point for transmission with 70.1% of the total cases reported followed by Gyeongbuk with 13.8% of the total cases reported. Looking at recent activity, for the 1st time in several weeks, yesterday (24 Mar 2020) Daegu did not report 40% or more of the newly confirmed cases, but only reported 14.0% of the newly confirmed cases in the preceding 24 hours. Today it reported 25%, significantly reduced from prior days. Increases in the proportion of newly confirmed case reporting were seen in Seoul at 12.5%, Gyeonggi at 13.5%, and Gyeongbuk at 11.5%. Quarantined imported cases represented 28.9% of the newly confirmed cases.

Similar to what is being seen in China, Korea is identifying increasing numbers of imported cases returning to South Korea. They are now up to 131 imported cases in quarantine with the 1st report of patients in quarantine on 16 Mar 2020, when 4 cases were reported (COVID-19 update (41): global, surge capacity, vaccine development, WHO 20200316.7096222). Like in China, there is strict surveillance and follow-up of these individuals, reversing the pattern of the western countries strengthening screenings of individuals from South Korea and China. There are obvious concerns regarding initiating new clusters that might escape into the community.

An English language MOH report from 25 Mar 2020 (https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=&bid=0030) has information on the origin of the imported cases over the past 3 days:

Date: 23 Mar 2020 / 24 Mar 2020 / 25 Mar 2020
Total confirmed cases: 64 / 76 / 100
Total confirmed imported cases: 18 (28.2%) / 25 (32.9%) / 51 (51.0%)
Europe: 7 / 20 / 29 (59.8% of 3 day total)
USA: 11 / 5 / 13 (30.9% of 3 day total)
Others: 0 / 0 / 9 (9.6% of 3 day total)
It would be interesting to see similar data from China. - Mod.MPP]

