C. Iran: 27 017 cases, 2077 deaths
Date: Wed 25 Mar 2020 20:12 GST
Source: Gulf News, [abridged, edited]
https://gulfnews.com/world/mena/coronavirus-iran-death-toll-rises-to-2077-with-cases-up-to-27017-1.1585152912065


Iran's coronavirus death toll has risen to 2077 after reporting 143 new fatalities, the Ministry of Health announced on Wednesday [25 Mar 2020]. "The country has reported 2206 new COVID-19 cases, bringing the total number of infections to 27 017," said Health Ministry's spokesperson Kianoush Jahanpour in a press conference on coronavirus updates.

He said 9625 previously infected people have already recovered. With the number of deaths exceeding 2000, Iran is now the world's 6th worst -- hit country by the potentially fatal pandemic after Italy, China, US, Spain, and Germany.

[Byline: Khitam Al Amir]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the 24 hours from 24 to 25 Mar 2020, the number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran grew from 24 811 to 27 017, an increase of 2206 newly confirmed cases. The number of deaths has also increased from 1934 to 2077 an increase of 143 deaths in the 24-hour period.

As I have mentioned for the past few days, the significant translocation of the population for the holidays is of concern as it may lead to continued intra country/provincial exportations of the virus. According to other media reports, the planned strategy for the next phase of containment is to prevent internal dislocations in the country, through a country-wide "stay at home" (https://hotair.com/archives/john-s-2/2020/03/25/irans-coronavirus-death-toll-passes-2000-new-travel-restrictions-put-place/).

