[Cruise ships have continued to maintain a focus as a source of transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 in this pandemic. The cruise ship industry has virtually come to a halt in the Americas, Europe, and Northern Western Pacific region. From the media reports out of Australia and New Zealand, they are still active. It sounds like both New Zealand and Australia have chains of transmission related to passengers from cruise ships who disembarked at stops as well as at final ports on return. The SARS-CoV-2 is not a nice virus, it spreads easily and insidiously through communities once it gets the chance. - Mod.MPP

