B. Submission on 1st case in St Lucia by medical student
Date: Wed 25 Mar 2020
From: Vaishnavee Vilas Wagh <vaishnaveewagh875@gmail.com>
and Sambaivarao Yaragalla <siva@spartanmed.org> [edited]


St Lucia records 1st case of COVID-19 on [11 Mar 2020]. Health Minister Mary Isaac at news conference confirmed that a 63-year-old British female, with travel history from the United Kingdom entered St Lucia from Grenada with her husband via British Airways on [7 Mar 2020]. The woman presented to St Lucia health care system on [11 Mar 2020]. The clinical samples were sent to the Caribbean Public Health Agency on the same day [11 Mar 2020]. The results were received on Friday [13 Mar 2020]. She tested positive for COVID-19.

As per the established protocol for management of COVID-19,she was placed in isolation at medical facility, looking at the travel history and presented symptoms her immediate contacts were also quarantined for 14 days before the signs and symptoms appear.

The Ministry of Health issued a release today [25 Mar 2020] which stated, "The patient has since been repatriated to the United Kingdom on 24 and 25 Mar 2020."

